<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-03T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="868" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Moose, James/423: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-03T13:00:00-04:00">May 3,
                                    1943—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>612. Personal for the Minister. Department’s 536, April 14, 5 p.m. The
                            President desires me to express to you his thanks and appreciation for
                            the services which you have rendered as Minister to Saudi Arabia.</p>
                        <p>Your resignation in that capacity will become effective upon the day when
                            your successor presents his letters of credence.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>